4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor

Effective writing is all about getting your message across to your audience as clearly as possible and leaving them wanting for more.

As modern day writers adapt to the latest AI powered text generators like ChatGPT that generate verbose text on any given topic, which is overall a great enhancement but essentially it lacks a personal touch and therefore has low impact on the reader.

In order to produce content that provides value to the reader we need to use these AI tools differently by aligning them with the principles of effective writing.

In this article we are going to talk about the 4 basic ideas of effective writing as shared by ex-wall street journal editor shani raja we have also linked his free course which will help you master the art of impactful writing.

First, Simplicity :

Idea: The whole point of this idea is to make your writing easier to read and deliver the information that you intend to and not to leave your reader scratching their head to get what you mean.

Practice:

Shorten the text and reduce flak: Trim excess words and unnecessary details to convey your message more succinctly, ensuring your writing remains concise and to the point.

Use easy words, simple familiar words: Choose words that are commonly understood by your audience, avoiding complex terminology that may confuse readers.

metadata.title: 4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx

chunks.text:
This promotes clarity and accessibility in your writing.

Uncomplicate your ideas: Break down complex concepts into simpler, digestible components, making it easier for readers to grasp the main points without feeling overwhelmed by unnecessary intricacies.

Remove jargon: Eliminate specialised terminology or industry-specific jargon that may be unfamiliar to your audience, replacing it with clear, everyday language to enhance understanding and engagement.

Examples:

Text: In the light of the extent, scale, range and immeasurable complexity of

the uncertainties that persist on the economic front,

we conclude, having evaluated the country's mid-to-long-term prospects, that multifarious scenarios could yet unfold.”

Simplified: With so much uncertainty surrounding the economy, anything

could happen,

Text: It is imperative that we engage in proactive measures to mitigate the potential risks associated with the implementation of new policies.

Simplified: We need to take action now to reduce the risks of new policies.

Second, Clarity :

Idea: In writing with clarity the whole point is to present your message as clearly as possible, so that your reader doesn’t have to struggle to understand you.

Practice: Think and then write, not write as you think.

Clarify your thoughts before writing:

Before beginning to write, ensure that your ideas are clear and well-defined in your mind.

metadata.source_url: uploaded_file://4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx
metadata.title: 4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx

chunks.text:
Take the time to organise your thoughts, outline your arguments, and clarify any uncertainties.

Don’t assume that your reader is an expert:

Avoid assuming prior knowledge on the part of your reader. Instead, aim for clarity and accessibility by explaining concepts and providing necessary context.

metadata.source_url: uploaded_file://4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx
metadata.title: 4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx

chunks.text:
This approach ensures that your writing is inclusive and understandable to a broader audience.

Examples:

Text: Plunging coal exports forced a sharp drop in government revenue this year, economists say.

Clarified: Government revenue dropped as tax collection dipped, due to low exports of coal this year, economists say.

Businesses exported less coal this year resulting in lower income and therefore, lower taxes which resulted in a sharp drop in government revenue, economists say.

Plunging coal exports meant producers earned less and thus contributed less tax, triggering a sharp drop in government revenue this year, economists say.

Third, Elegance:

Idea : The writing should flow, the sentences and paragraphs should connect with one another so that the meaning is not lost.

Practice: Flow the text should flow as cause and effect.

Make your text less cluttered with punctuations and separate paragraphs when needed.

Example:

Qantas reported record profit.

metadata.source_url: uploaded_file://4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx
metadata.title: 4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx

chunks.text:
The airline said it was pleased with the result. Qantas is planning to increase the number of routes it flies. The carrier hopes that doing so will boost future earnings.

Qantas reported record profit and said it was pleased with the result. To help boost future earnings, the airline is planning to increase the number of routes it flies."

Fourth, Evocativeness:

Idea is to make writing more memorable and make it interesting to read.

metadata.source_url: uploaded_file://4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx
metadata.title: 4 Tips for effective writing from ex-wall street journal editor.docx

chunks.text:
The reader should be able to form a mental picture as they are reading.

Practice: avoid repetition by using variety of sentences

Use active voice mainly but passive only when necessary

Example:

The company was told by the regulators to hand over the documents.

The regulator told the company to hand over the documents.

It seems that Apple’s earnings this time around are less than impressive.

Apple’s earnings this time around are less than impressive.

Apple’s earnings this time around are unimpressive.
